Brazil, Norway Post 1-0 Wins in Opening Games at Women’s Soccer World Cup

-- B y   P e t e r - J o s e p h   H e g a r t y
-- 
2011-06-29T18:15:25Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-29/norway-beats-equatorial-guinea-1-0-in-women-s-world-cup-match.html
Brazil  and  Norway  won 1-0 today in
their opening games at soccer’s Women’s World Cup in  Germany .  Rosana scored in the 54th minute as Brazil, runner-up
to Germany at the last World Cup four years ago, beat  Australia 
in Moenchengladbach. In the other Group D match in Augsburg,
1995 champion Norway defeated  Equatorial Guinea  on Emilie
Haavi’s goal with six minutes remaining.  Tomorrow, Group A leader Germany, which has won the past
two World Cups, plays  Nigeria  in  Frankfurt  am Main.  Canada  meets
 France  in Bochum.  The 16 teams are split into four groups with the top two in
each progressing to the quarterfinals. The final of the four-
yearly  soccer tournament  is on July 17.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Peter-Joseph Hegarty in  London  at 
 phegarty@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
 Christopher Elser  at   celser@bloomberg.net . 